<TITLE> Bomb attack wounds three Algerian soldiers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ALGIERS, Dec 24 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Three Algerian soldiers were seriously wounded when a bomb explosion hit their convoy in eastern Algeria, a security source said on Monday. The bomb went off on Sunday when the convoy drove through an area near the eastern town of Tebessa, 600 km (375 miles) from the capital Algiers, the source said. The attack came one day after the army defused three home-made bombs near a military checkpoint in the troubled Kabylie region, the source added. Two car bombs killed at least 37 people, including 11 U.N. employee staff in Algiers on Dec.11. Algeria plunged into violence in 1992 after the then military-backed government scrapped legislative elections which the Islamic Salvation Front (FIS), a radical Islamic party, was poised to win. An estimated 200,000 people were killed since then. The violence had subsided since the 1990s but in the past twelve months has regained some of its former intensi
